Kenya Under-19 poor run at the Under-19 Cricket World Cup continued when they lost to Namibia by eight wickets in their Plate semi-final play-off at Lincoln Green, Christchurch, on Thursday. Put in to bat first Kenya set a target of 177 all out in 36.5 overs. Aman Gandhi top scored for Kenya with 52 runs that came off 80 balls with two boundaries. Aveet Desai (32 off 59 balls with three boundaries), Ankit Hirani (20) and Jayant Mepani(15) and Jasraj Kundi (14) off 33 balls with a boundary and a six) were Kenya’s other batsmen who posted double digit scores.   Sri Lanka were third in Group “D” with two points.